<plot>News correspondent, Hie-jeong, is sent to Japan. There she employs Sang-jun as her guide and interpreter. Sang-jun is also working with North Korean agents who want to kidnap the outspoken reporter. Hie-jeong is angered by the sensationalism of the Japanese press and denounces it during a live television interview with a politician. Impressed by her courage, Sang-jun begins to have doubts about his mission.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?041847</url></doc>
